A '''fin de fiesta''' is a short theatrical piece in the [[Spanish Golden Age]] (Siglo de Oro) tradition performed after the [[comedia (Spanish play)|''comedia'']] in order to send the audience home in a festive mood.<ref name="BernalPeña1998">{{cite book|author1=Concepción Reverte Bernal|author2=Mercedes de los Reyes Peña|title=II Congreso Iberoamericano de Teatro: América y el Teatro Español del Siglo de Oro: Cádiz, 23 a 26 de octubre, 1996|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JaQTBUKYfSgC&pg=PA370|accessdate=23 August 2013|year=1998|publisher=Servicio Publicaciones UCA|language=Spanish|isbn=978-84-7786-536-0|pages=370–}}</ref> This was first performed in 1798.<ref name="Tejera2007">{{cite book|author=María del Carmen García Tejera|title=Lecturas del pensamiento filosófico, estético y político|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=od8ZvAGUxr8C&pg=PA73|accessdate=23 August 2013|year=2007|publisher=Servicio Publicaciones UCA|language=Spanish|isbn=978-84-9828-158-3|pages=73–}}</ref>

